reviews.text: I had my daughter's graduation party here and it turned out awesome. Food was great. Service was excellent. The ladies that set up the food n handled all that were great also.  The tables were perfectly set. Stefanie was so helpful through the whole process. All the guests loved it.

Stopped in for an early dinner. Food was fantastic love the taste of the coal fired pizza, had a good crispy to it without being too well done, definitely worth trying. Got a side of meatballs, and they were so light and fluffy more like cake, also very good. Place is not a traditional pizza place, it more on the side of ‚Äúfine dining‚Äù as everyone there was dressed up and eating pizza with forks and knives, all I can say about that is we didn‚Äôt fit in. We did feel rushed to leave by the young waitress.

First time here and loved it, pizzas very distinct from the usual and excellent in every regard. The sauce, cheeses used, and toppings were all fantastic. The crust is perfect, crispy outside and just the right amount of chewy inside.
We tried the Italian wings, again different from the usual and very very good. Crispy skin and moist/tender inside. Nicely seasoned.
Good drinks, wife enjoyed a White Cosmo and I had the Italian margarita. Tajin rim on the margarita was new to me and I loved it.
Finished with a generous Tiramisu and Sambuca.
Plenty leftover to enjoy at home. We‚Äôll gladly travel the 30 minutes to come again.

Fettuccine with vodka sauce lacked any flavor. My wife's  Mac & cheese with bacon tasted good, but where's the bacon? Got charged an extra dollar for 1/2 bacon. It comes with bacon. Garlic rolls? No garlic, just butter & sprinkled cheese on top.Drinks are expensive 6.25 each for an IPA. 7.95 for a Bellini_ Tini. I didn't even get a full glass of my first beer because that was the end of the pumpkin. Krista M was on the spot for our waitress. My first visit was non impressive. I have been to only 1 other restaurant where a salad is not part of a dinner meal. So this is strike 2. I play ball but not that it matters. I don't see a third try. Each their own I get it.Service is great!

This is one of my mother‚Äòs favorite pizza places. We‚Äôve dine in and take out frequently. The outdoor patio is great when the weather permits. Fantastic pizza one of the best in the area. We‚Äôve had the Buffalo chicken pizza, pepperoni, pizza, anchovy pizza, plain pizza, and all are wonderful. The flank steak sandwich is marinated perfectly- lots of flavor and deliciousness in every bite. The salads are huge, fresh & delightful. The mac & cheese with bacon and bread crumbs is phenomenal. There certainly is something for everyone. The menu is full of excellent choices. They have a very nicely appointed private room for parties, gatherings and special occasions. It‚Äôs a very popular place. We‚Äôve always received our dishes promptly and without delay. Great choice

detailedReviews.text: Waiters have no coordination, it seemed like one out of the 6 or 7 working had any experience serving food.. took over 10 minutes for one of them to ask what we wanted to drink. Once we received dirty plates we decided to get our food to go but should have just left because they brought food out one by one for the next 15 minutes instead of all at once so everything was cold except the last item they brought out. The place is messy, and outdated...waiters dropped two things on the ground in less than an hour, leaving food on the floor that you had to walk around before leaving. Pizza tasted like it was made with ketchup and bagged cheddar cheese with extra salt. Never received a check either, the waiter just told us how much we owed them.
